# Edulamad (fork of Nsuo stack) — frontend rules

## Product context

- Platform: **Edulamad** — AI-assisted past questions and exam prep for Ghanaian universities (see product brief). This repo still carries Nsuo-era farm routes in places; rebrand user-facing copy via `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME` (default **Edulamad**).
- Legacy reference: `Prompt-main.md`, `prompt.md`, `contexts/api-docs.json` describe the **backend HTTP contract** until Edulamad’s API diverges.
- Backend contract: `contexts/api-docs.json` (Swagger). Do not invent endpoints or fields.

## Core stack (from project rules)

- Next.js 15 Pages Router, TypeScript where used, Tailwind, TanStack Query v5, Zustand, TanStack Table v8, RHF + Zod, Axios via `apiClient`, Recharts, existing Redux until migrated.
- Non‑negotiables: no `any`; no raw axios; no `useEffect` for server data (use Query); orgId only from auth store; permissions via `hasPermission`.

## UI / UX Pro Max (Cursor skill)

- Project skill: `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`.
- For UI/UX work, run design-system search from repo root, for example:
  `python3 .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product> <industry> <keywords>" --design-system -p "Nsuo"`
- Prefer persisted design docs only when the user wants a long-lived design system (`--persist` per that skill).

## Motion (Framer Motion)

- Use `framer-motion` for enter/exit, layout, and micro-interactions.
- Avoid hydration mismatches: gate client-only motion with `use client` boundaries if migrating to App Router; in Pages Router, avoid animating from random or time-based initial state on the server; prefer `initial={false}` or mount-gated animation when SSR output must match first paint.

## Icons

- Default: `lucide-react` (aligned with existing app).
- Also available: `react-icons` for sets not in Lucide (e.g. brand icons). Keep imports tree-shake friendly (named imports per icon family).

## 21st.dev

- Package: `@21st-sdk/react` — chat/agent UI primitives; see https://21st.dev/agents
- When using those components, import styles once (e.g. in `pages/_app.js`): `@21st-sdk/react/styles.css` or `./styles/index.css` per package docs.

## Ship gate

- Do not push if `npm run build` fails or if ESLint reports errors. Fix hydration warnings on critical paths before merging UI changes.
